    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are given a set of news articles grouped by topic and time window.\n\nEach article has:\n- id\n- source\n- title\n- content\n- event_time\n\nTask:\n- Identify real-world incidents described by at least TWO articles.\n- Produce one object per incident.\n- Include ONLY articles describing the SAME incident.\n\nInput:\n{{ JSON.stringify($json.records) }}\n\nOutput format (STRICT JSON):\n[\n  {\n    \"incident_key\": \"<stable_key>\",\n    \"incident_title\": \"<concise title>\",\n    \"incident_summary\": [\n      \"<bullet 1>\",\n      \"<bullet 2>\"\n    ],\n    \"topic\": \"{{ $json.topic }}\",\n    \"signals\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"<id>\",\n        \"source\": \"<source>\",\n        \"title\": \"<title>\",\n        \"content\": \"<content>\",\n        \"event_time\": \"<event_time>\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"confidence\": 0.0\n  }\n]\n\nIf no incidents are found, return [].",
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "message": "You are an incident correlation engine.\n\nYour job is to identify REAL-WORLD INCIDENTS, not themes.\n\nDefinition:\n- An incident is ONE specific real-world event\n  (announcement, rollout, policy change, lawsuit, outage, enforcement action).\n- An incident MUST be supported by AT LEAST TWO DISTINCT SOURCES.\n\nSTRICT RULES:\n- You MUST verify at least two DIFFERENT sources per incident.\n- Do NOT cluster by topic, hype, sentiment, or general discussion.\n- Do NOT invent connections.\n- If unsure, return [].\n\nTOPIC HANDLING:\n- You MUST NOT invent or change the topic.\n- Use ONLY the provided topic value.\n- If an incident clearly spans domains, keep the topic unchanged\n  and add a short note explaining the cross-domain nature.\n\nOUTPUT RULE:\n- If no valid incident exists, return [].\n- Return JSON only. No prose."
            }
          ]
        },
